



Sir,
Annapolis Sepr 24th 1771



At the particular request of the Honble Danl Dulany Esqr., I address this Letter to youa certain Mr Plowman of Baltimore has, unfortunately, had his Vessel siezd by the Boston Frigate, if it should be condemnd, I have to request the favour of you to facilitate the purchase of it & render any Service you can in behalf of the proprietor1I have no great right to take this Liberty, but you will be good enough, I hope, to excuse the freedom taken by Sir Yr Most Obedt Servt

Go: Washington

